org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client

Class AsyncRegionReplicaReplayRetryingCaller

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client.AsyncRpcRetryingCaller<Long>
      • org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client.AsyncRegionReplicaReplayRetryingCaller

  • @InterfaceAudience.Private
public class AsyncRegionReplicaReplayRetryingCaller
extends AsyncRpcRetryingCaller<Long>
    For replaying edits for region replica.

    The mainly difference here is that, every time after locating, we will check whether the region name is equal, if not, we will give up, as this usually means the region has been split or merged, and the new region(s) should already have all the data of the parent region(s).

    Notice that, the return value is the edits we skipped, as the original response message is not used at upper layer.
